text: James Stables (November 25, 1860 – February 17, 1926) was a Scottish-Canadian politician. He served in the Legislative Assembly of British Columbia from 1900 to 1903 from the electoral district of Cassiar. ==Election results== ==References== Category:Scottish emigrants to Canada Category:1860 births Category:1926 deaths Category:Members of the Legislative Assembly of British Columbia
title: James Stables
